developer_response:
It is not true.

We are planning add into the store only cosmetic items that do not affect the gameplay. 
Currently the store has: 
- Mounts (you can also tame them in the game without buying anything); 
- Titles (the word to be written in front of your name, for example, "Baron Kevan", "Duke Kevan", etc.). Does not affect the gameplay; 
- Booster that increases speed of resource gathering and construction time (reduces only time spent on the action. For example, if you collect apples for 2 seconds, then having a booster, you will collect them for 1 second); 

That's all there is at the moment in the game store. We do not plan to add "pay2win". We believe that this model is doomed to failure. 
We decided to make the shop only in order that players can additionally thank us if they liked the game. Whereas in the buy-to-play is impossible.
